The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi/London, Dec. 15: HCL Technologies has completed the acquisition of Axon Group Plc, the UK-based consulting firm, for 441.1 million. The merger of Axon and HCLs SAP practice will bring new capabilities into the market, HCL Tech chief Vineet Nayar said. Last week, a London court had given the go-ahead to Axon to be acquired by HCL Technologies.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: Drug price regulator National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority will monitor price fluctuation limits of non-scheduled drugs based on new prices, which were reduced after the governments recent 4 per cent Cenvat cut.                            
	 Bangalore, Dec. 15: Infosys has received a five-year global sourcing order from pharmaceutical company AstraZeneca. Infosys will deliver application maintenance services to AstraZenecas global operations.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: The Centre will convene a meeting between jute mill owners and trade unions on Wednesday to resolve the ongoing indefinite strike in the industry.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: Aviva Life Insurance is expecting its new premium business to grow up to 35 per cent next year against 9 per cent this fiscal.                                                                                                                         
